The paper deals with approximation algorithms for covering problems in metric spaces, which are fundamental topics in theoretical computer science. The use of star covers and balanced loads suggests that the paper may belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS) or computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves optimization and approximation techniques, which are relevant to the categories of game theory (cs.GT), machine learning (cs.LG), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
